Date: Tue 4 Aug 2015
Source: OIE, WAHID weekly disease information 2015; 28(32) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=18296


Foot-and-mouth disease, Botswana
--------------------------------
Information received on 4 Aug 2015 from Dr Letlhogile Modisa, Director, Veterinary Services, Ministry of Agriculture, Gaborone, Botswana

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 3 Aug 2015
Date of confirmation of the event: 3 Aug 2015
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 20 May 2015
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: foot-and-mouth disease virus
Serotype: pending
Nature of diagnosis: clinical
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Gubago Crush, Shorobe Extension Area, Zone 2D, Ngamiland, Ngamiland [North-West district]
Date of start of the outbreak: 3 Aug 2015
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 170 / 26 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: cattle grazing in a communal area adjacent to zone 16 within zone 2D.
Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 15.29 / 0 / 0 / 0
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: illegal movement of animals; contact with wild species
Epidemiological comments: cattle having clinical signs consistent with foot and mouth disease (FMD) were found after a report by the farmer in zone 2D. Cattle had teat, feet, and mouth lesions consistent with FMD. Laboratory investigation and field epidemiological investigations are on-going. Weekly reports will be provided.

Control measures
Measures applied: control of wildlife reservoirs; movement control inside the country; disinfection/disinfestations; surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; traceability; no vaccination, no treatment of affected animals.
Measures to be applied: vaccination in response to the outbreak(s).

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Botswana Vaccine Institute (OIE's reference laboratory) / Cattle / virus isolation / - / Pending

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

